Author-Name:    Bowman, David
Author-Name:  Faust, Jon
Title:   Options, Sunspots, and the Creation of Uncertainty. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 957-75
Issue: 5
Volume: 105
Year: 1997
Month:  October 
Abstract:
  The authors present two examples in which the addition of an option
 market leads to sunspot equilibria despite the fact that no sunspot
 equilibria exist without the market. These examples highlight limitations
 in two prevalent views of option markets. It is often assumed that option
 markets help complete otherwise incomplete markets. The authors
 demonstrate that they can instead increase the number of events agents
 wish to insure against. As in Fischer Black and Myron Scholes (1973), it
 is often assumed that option markets are redundant. The authors
 demonstrate that an option market may not be redundant even when markets
 were complete before its introduction.   Copyright 1997 by the University of Chicago.
